definition: double/twice/simultaneous/holding two or more (official) posts at the same time
difference/discrepancy/to differ/error/to err/to make a mistake
to differ from/to fall short of/lacking/wrong/inferior/Taiwan pr. [cha1]

sentences.english: He takes a part-time job as a cashier.
sentences.chinese: 他利用工作的空馀时间兼差做收银员。

sentences.english: Policemen with families have to moonlight to make ends meet.
sentences.chinese: 有家室的警察必须兼差才能维持家计。

sentences.english: There're no part-time jobs at the moment.
sentences.chinese: 目前没有兼差做的工作。

sentences.english: If you're a servant of God, you can't moonlight for yourself.
sentences.chinese: 假如你是神的仆人，你不能同时兼差为自己而活。

sentences.english: These workers moonlight to live on a higher plane.
sentences.chinese: 些工人靠兼差来提高生活水平。

sentences.english: While working my way through graduate school, I taught five-string banjo in a music store.
sentences.chinese: 我念研究所时，在一间乐器行兼差教授五弦琴。

sentences.english: I will have to start moonlighting to make both ends meet.
sentences.chinese: 我得要开始兼差才能让收支平衡些。

sentences.english: Victor:I will have to start moonlighting to make both ends meet.
sentences.chinese: 我得要开始兼差才能让收支平衡些。

sentences.english: He got a part-time job washing dishes.
sentences.chinese: 他得到一份洗碗碟的兼差工作。
